Name: Albany Hwy, Williams
Description: The road surface condition on Albany Highway, esp. the section 100km either side of Williams town site suffers from significant pavement defects which can destablise a vehicle.  These have been present since the last grain harvest season and have been excacerbated by the use of road transport for grain cartage to the Williams CBH terminal - related to recent closures of rail?. We are about to start the 18/19 grain season and last years potholes and ruts still haven't been fixed.
